ates (New York City)\n* [[Charles Chartier]] (1940\u20131967)\n* [[Jean-Marc Roy]] (1967\u20131969)\n* G\u00e9n\u00e9ral [[Jean V. Allard]] (1969\u20131971)\n* [[Guy Poliquin]] (1971\u20131977)\n* [[Marcel Bergeron]] (delegate general) (1977\u20131980)\n* Richard Pouliot (delegate general) (1980\u20131982)\n* Raymond Gosselin (delegate general) (1982\u20131984)\n* Rita Dionne-Marsolais (delegate general) (1984\u20131987)\n* [[L\u00e9o Par\u00e9]] (delegate general) (1987\u20131992)\n* Reed Scowen (delegate general) (1992\u20131994)\n* [[Kevin Drummond]] (delegate general) (1994\u20131997)\n* David Levine (delegate general) (1997\u20131998)\n* Diane Wilhelmy (delegate general) (1998\u20132002)\n* Michel Robitaille (delegate general) (2002\u20132007)\n* [[Bruno Fortier]] (delegate general) (2007\u20132008)\n* Robert Keating (delegate general) (2008\u20132009)\n* John Parisella (delegate general) (2009\u20132012)\n* [[Andr\u00e9 Boisclair]] (delegate general) (2012\u20132013)\n* [[Dominique Poirier]] (delegate general) (2013\u20132014)\n* Jean-Claude Lauzon (delegate general) (2014\u2013present)<ref name=ag/>\n\n===Agents-general for Saskatchewan===\n* [[Graham Spry]] (1946\u20131968)\n* [[Edward Arthur Boden]] (1973\u20131977)\n* [[Merv Johnson]] (1977\u20131983)\n* Robert Larter\n* [[Paul Emile Rousseau]] (1986\u20131991)\n\n==Malta==\n* Hon. Sir [[James Connolly (Australian politician)|James Connolly]], 1929\u20131932\n* Dr Constantine John Colombos, 1922-1927 & 1932-1933\n\n==Jamaica==\nSource: ''Historic Jamaica''.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/stream/cu31924020417527#page/n29/mode/2up |title=Historic Jamaica |first=Frank |last=Cundall |page=xxiii |publisher=The West India Committee |location=London |year=1915 |accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref>\n* 1664\u20131666: Sir James Modyford\n* 1682\u2013?: [[Sir Charles Lyttelton, 3rd Baronet|Sir Charles Lyttelton]]\n* William Beeston\n* 1688: Ralph Knight\n* Gilbert Heathcote\n* 1693\u20131704: Bartholomew Gracedieu\n* 1714: P. Marsh\n* 1725: Alexander Stephenson\n* 1725\u20131726: Edward Charlton\n* 1728\u20131733: Charles de la Foy\n* 1733: John Gregory\n* 1733\u20131757: John Sharpe\n* 1757\u20131762: Lovell Stanhope (MP for [[Winchester (UK Parliament constituency)|Winchester]])\n* 1764\u20131795: Stephen Fuller\n* 1795\u20131803: Robert Sewell\n* 1803\u20131812: Edmund Pusey Lyon\n* 1812\u20131831: [[George Hibbert]]\n* 1831\u20131845: [[William Burge]]\n* 1845 ''Office abolished''\n\n==Orange River Colony==\nThe [[Orange River Colony]] sent an agent-general from 108 until the creation of the [[Union of South Africa]] in 1910. Brounger was a former Director of the [[Central South African Railways|Orange Free State Railways]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#FFCC33\"\n! Agents-General !! Years !! Notes\n|-\n| [[Richard Ernest Brounger]] || August 1908 \u2013 31 May 1910 ||<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article156569643 |title=News in Brief. |newspaper=[[The Gloucester Advocate]] |location=New South Wales, Australia |date=22 August 1908 |access-date=11 April 2020 |page=2 |via=Trove }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Transvaal Colony==\nThe [[Transvaal Colony]] sent an agent-general from the establishment of responsible self-government in 1907 until the creation of the Union of South Africa in 1910. Solomon the served as the first South African High Commissioner in London from 1910 to 1913.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#FFCC33\"\n! Agents-General !! Years !! Notes\n|-\n| [[Richard Solomon (barrister)|Sir Richard Solomon]] || 3 May 1907 \u2013 31 May 1910 ||<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article198620601 |title=GENERAL CABLE NEWS. |newspaper=[[The Age]] |location=Victoria, Australia |date=4 May 1907 |access-date=11 April 2020 |page=13 |via=Trove }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article14863329 |title=GENERAL CABLE NEWS. |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |location=New South Wales, Australia |date=26 March 1907 |access-date=10 April 2020 |page=7 |via=Trove }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article14879874 |title=SECOND EDITION. The King's Birthday. Presentation of the Cullinan Diamond. |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |location=New South Wales, Australia |date=11 November 1907 |access-date=10 April 2020 |page=5 |via=Trove }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Cape Colony==\nThe [[Cape Colony]] sent separate agents-general until the creation of the Union of South Africa in 1910.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#FFCC33\"\n! Agents-General !! Years !! Notes\n|-\n| [[Charles Mills (civil servant)|Sir Charles Mills]] || October 1882 \u2013 31 March 1895 ||<ref>{{cite DNB|wstitle=Mills, Charles (1825-1895)|last=Harris|first=Charles Alexander|pages=175\u2013176|volume=3|supplement=1}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[David Tennant (politician)|Sir David Tennant]] || 1896 \u2013 31 December 1901 ||<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article193467839 |title=CAPE COLONY'S AGENT. GENERAL. |newspaper=The Age |location=Victoria, Australia |date=15 April 1895 |access-date=11 April 2020 |page=5 |via=Trove }}</ref><ref>{{London Gazette |issue=26980|supp=y|date=22 June 1898|page=3853}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Thomas Ekins Fuller|Sir Thomas Ekins Fuller]] || 1 January 1902 \u2013 31 December 1907 ||<ref>{{cite DNB|wstitle=Fuller, Thomas Ekins|last=Hillier|first=Alfred Peter|pages=59\u201360|volume=1|supplement=2}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Somerset Richard French|Sir Somerset Richard French]] || 1 January 1908 \u2013 31 May 1910 ||<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article37564218 |title=CAPE'S NEW AGENT-GENERAL. |newspaper=Western Mail |location=Western Australia |date=18 January 1908 |access-date=11 April 2020 |page=44 |via=Trove }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Natal==\nThe [[Colony of Natal]] sent separate agents-general until the creation of the Union of South Africa in 1910.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#FFCC33\"\n! Agents-General !! Years !! Notes\n|-\n| [[Walter Peace|Sir 