l |publisher=Addison-Wesley |isbn=0-201-83454-5 }}\n* {{Cite book |first=Scott |last=Meyers |authorlink=Scott Meyers |year=2005 |title=Effective C++ |edition=Third |publisher=Addison-Wesley |isbn=0-321-33487-6 |url=https://archive.org/details/effectivec55spec00meye }}\n* {{Cite book |first=Bjarne |last=Stroustrup|authorlink=Bjarne Stroustrup |year=2013 |title=[[The C++ Programming Language]] |edition=Fourth |publisher=Addison-Wesley |isbn=978-0-321-56384-2 }}\n* {{Cite book |first=Bjarne |last=Stroustrup|authorlink=Bjarne Stroustrup |year=1994 |title=[[The Design and Evolution of C++]] |publisher=Addison-Wesley |isbn=0-201-54330-3 }}\n* {{Cite book |first=Bjarne |last=Stroustrup|authorlink=Bjarne Stroustrup|year=2014 |title=Programming: Principles and Practice Using C++ |edition=Second |publisher=Addison-Wesley |isbn=978-0-321-99278-9 }}\n* {{Cite book |first=Herb |last=Sutter|authorlink=Herb Sutter |year=2001 |title=More Exceptional C++: 40 New Engineering Puzzles, Programming Problems, and Solutions |publisher=Addison-Wesley |isbn=0-201-70434-X }}\n* {{Cite book |first=Herb |last=Sutter|authorlink=Herb Sutter |year=2004 |title=Exceptional C++ Style |publisher=Addison-Wesley |isbn=0-201-76042-8 }}\n* {{Cite book |first=David |last=Vandevoorde |first2=Nicolai M. |last2=Josuttis |year=2003 |title=C++ Templates: The complete Guide |publisher=Addison-Wesley |isbn=0-201-73484-2 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Sister project links|n=no|s=no|b=Subject:C++ programming language}}\n* [http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/ JTC1/SC22/WG21]{{snd}} the ISO/IEC C++ Standard Working Group\n* [https://isocpp.org/ Standard C++ Foundation]{{snd}} a non-profit organization that promotes the use and understanding of standard C++. Bjarne Stroustrup is a director of the organization.\n\n{{ISO standards}}\n{{Programming languages}}\n{{C++ programming language}}\n{{List of International Electrotechnical Commission standards}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:C}}\n[[Category:Algol programming language family]]\n[[Category:C++| ]]\n[[Category:C++ programming language family]]\n[[Category:Class-based programming languages]]\n[[Category:Cross-platform software]]\n[[Category:High-level programming languages]]\n[[Category:Object-oriented programming languages]]\n[[Category:Programming languages created in 1983]]\n[[Category:Programming languages with an ISO standard]]\n[[Category:Statically typed programming languages]]\n", "name_user": "Bellowhead678", "label": "safe", "comment": "acompanied->accompanied -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2B"}
{"title_page": "Mar\u00eda Bel\u00f3n", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Mar\u00eda Bel\u00f3n\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1966|05|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Madrid]], [[Spain]]\n| nationality = {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Spanish people|Spanish]]\n| years_active = 2011\u2013present\n| occupation  = {{flatlist|\n* Spokesperson\n* advocate\n}}\n| known_for   = Surviving the 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami\n| spouse      = Enrique Alv\u00e1rez\n| children    = Lucas, Sim\u00f3n and Tom\u00e1s\n}}\n\n'''Mar\u00eda Bel\u00f3n''' (born May 12, 1966) did a poo in da ocean<ref>[http://elpais.com/elpais/2013/02/13/eps/1360779765_791086.html Maria Belon story] accessed 3/21/2015</ref> is a Spanish physician and motivational speaker, known for surviving the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami]] when she was on vacation in Thailand with her husband Enrique (Quique) \u00c1lvarez<ref>[http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20666183,00.html Maria Belon: ''The Impossible''&rsquo;s Real-Life Survivor]</ref> and three sons Lucas, Sim\u00f3n and Tom\u00e1s \u00c1lvarez. She was severely injured in the tsunami and nearly died.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://voices.yahoo.com/tsunami-survivor-maria-belon-reflects-impossible-11937174.html?cat=40 |title=Tsunami Survivor Maria Belon Reflects on 'The Impossible' |first=Ben |last=Kenberr |work=voices.yahoo.com |date=14 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130124035640/http://voices.yahoo.com/tsunami-survivor-maria-belon-reflects-impossible-11937174.html?cat=40 |archive-date=24 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2252664/Boxing-Day-Tsunami-Family-relive-incredible-tale-survival-2004-tsunami-story-hits-big-screen.html |title=Boxing Day Tsunami': Family-of-five relive their incredible tale of survival in 2004 tsunami as story hits the big screen |first=Simon |last=Tomlinson |work=[[Mail Online]] |date=24 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nShe was portrayed in the 2012 film ''[[The Impossible (2012 film)|The Impossible]]'' by [[Naomi Watts]] (with the name changed to Bennett), who received a Best Actress [[Academy Award]] nomination for her performance.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://frontrowfeatures.com/2013/01/nothing-is-impossible-for-maria-belon/ |title=Maria Belon survived 'The Impossible' |first=Angela |last=Dawson |work=frontrowfeatures.com |date=3 January 2013 |accessdate=2 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130112080836/http://frontrowfeatures.com/2013/01/nothing-is-impossible-for-maria-belon/ |archive-date=12 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The family's nationality was unspecified in the film.<ref name=\"VeryAware\">{{cite web|last=Howard|first=Courtney|date=13 December 2012|url=http://veryaware.com/2012/12/interview-naomi-watts-ewan-mcgregor-j-a-bayona-sergio-g-sanchez-belen-atienza-maria-belon-talk-the-impossible/|title=INTERVIEW: Naomi Watts, Ewan McGregor, J.A. Bayona, Sergio G. S\u00e1nchez, Bel\u00e9n Atienza & Maria Belon Talk THE IMPOSSIBLE|work=Very Aware Movie Blog|accessdate=3 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121219041237/http://veryaware.com/2012/12/interview-naomi-watts-ewan-mcgregor-j-a-bayona-sergio-g-sanchez-belen-atienza-maria-belon-talk-the-impossible/|archive-date=19 December 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Movieline\">{{cite web|last=Randolph|first=Grace|date=13 December 2012|url=http://movieline.com/2012/12/13/watch-ewan-mcgregor-naomi-watts-talking-about-preparing-for-the-impossible/|title=WATCH: Ewan McGregor & Naomi Watts Talking About Preparing For 'The Impossible'|publisher=[[Movieline]]|accessdate=3 January 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Yahoo Voices\">{{cite web|date=14 December 2012|last=Kenber|first=Ben|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/tsunami-survivor-maria-belon-reflects-impossible-11937174.html|title=Tsunami Survivor Maria Belon Reflects on 'The Impossible'|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|accessdate=3 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140619151328/http://voices.yahoo.com/tsunami-survivor-maria-belon-reflects-impossible-11937174.html|archive-date=19 June 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Movies.ie\">{{cite web|date=31 December 2012|last=Hayes|first=Brogen|url=http://www.movies.ie/interviews/1186542/the_impossible__behind_the_scenes|title=THE IMPOSSIBLE \u2013 Behind The Scenes|publisher=Movies.ie|accessdate=3 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130103045504/http://www.movies.ie/Interviews/1186542/THE_IMPOSSIBLE__Behind_The_Scenes|archive-date=3 January 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nBel\u00f3n now travels around the world as an advocate for survivors of the tsunami and gives motivational speeches about how she overcame the turmoil and two years of recovery following her injuries. She studied to be a physician and also previously worked as a professor of management with the [[ESADE Business School]], and as a business consultant for companies like Pepsi. She has stated that some of her family is from the [[Canary Islands]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.grupobcc.com/files/conferenciantes/bio/Maria%20Belon.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-03-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403002912/http://www.grupobcc.com/files/conferenciantes/bio/Maria%20Belon.pdf |archivedate=2015-04-03 }} Maria Belon bio accessed 3/21/2015</ref>\n\nShe was the Spotlight Guest Speaker at the Share Iuvare Business Convention in 2015. Also in 2015 she was a speaker at the [[World Business Forum]]. In 2013 she was a guest lecturer at the Instituto de Cervantes in Gibraltar.<ref>[http://www.lomasrecomendable.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1892:maria-belon-una-vida-de-pelicula-en-world-business-forum-2015&catid=47:otros&Itemid=93 World Business Forum 2015]</ref>\n\n==Tsunami==\n{{BLP unsourced section|date=October 2016}}\nBel\u00f3n, a doctor, and her husband, Enrique \u00c1lvarez and her three sons, Lucas, Tomas and Simon were on Christmas vacation at a resort in [[Khao Lak]], Thailand. On December 26, 2004, Bel\u00f3n was at the poolside while her husband and three sons, Lucas, 10, Tom\u00e1s, 8, and Sim\u00f3n, 5, were splashing in the pool, before the family was swept apart by the tsunami.\n\nAfter the wave hit and swept her away from her family, she was able to grab hold of a tree with the aim of waiting for the tsunami to subside. While hanging on, however, she noticed her son Lucas in the distance being dragged by the current, screaming for help. She swam after him, but a second large wave occurred and she was dragged through a lot of rubble and hard sharp objects, and was critically wounded. After the tsunami calmed down, Bel\u00f3n was able to swim to land with Lucas, only to notice her many injuries. Her right leg was the most damaged, having been  completely ripped open, but she was able to dress her leg wound with palm tree leaves.\n\nBel\u00f3n and Lucas continued walking and looking for safety, but she was losing too much blood and her son had to help her walk. Lucas found a tree that the two could climb so that they would be safe from further waves. Maria was in too much pain to climb up the tree alone so Lucas, who had already climbed up, jumped down and helped her climb up the tree. After waiting on the tree for some time, the two were saved by locals from a nearby village who were coming to check the wreckage. Bel\u00f3n was then taken to a hospital, accompanied by her son.\n\nDuring his mother's recovery, Lucas was able to reunite with his father and two brothers, who happened to be in the hospital as well. Once she was stable enough to be moved, Bel\u00f3n and her family were transferred to a hospital in [[Singapore]], where she received more treatment and was finally able to return home.\n\n==Aftermath==\nBel\u00f3n is credited in the cast of the 2012 film ''[[The Impossible (2012 film)|The Impossible]]'' for providing her story and working on the set in [[Thailand]] in the same locations as the original tsunami.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2013/jan/03/reel-history-the-impossible |title=The Impossible submerges the true impact of the tsunami |first=Alex |last=von Tunzelmann |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=3 January 2013 |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group|GMG]] |location=[[London, England|London]] |issn=0261-3077 |oclc=60623878 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref> She spent time with Naomi Watts and helped her prepare for the role.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2214869/Naomi-Watts-shares-spotlight-tsunami-survivor-Maria-Madrid-premiere-The-Impossible.html |title=Naomi Watts shares the spotlight with tsunami survivor Maria at Madrid premiere of The Impossible |first=Emily |last=Sheridan |work=Mail Online |date=9 October 2012  |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref> Bel\u00f3n chose Naomi Watts to play her in the film, stating that Watts was her favorite actress after seeing the film ''[[21 Grams]]''. She worked with screenwriter [[Sergio G. S\u00e1nchez]] to ensure her story was accurately told.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.hitfix.com/the-fien-print/naomi-watts-found-real-life-inspiration-for-the-impossible |title=Naomi Watts discusses the real life inspiration for The Impossible |first=Daniel |last=Fienberg |work=[[HitFix]] |date=19 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crushable.com/2012/12/21/entertainment/the-impossible-true-story-maria-belon-enrique-belon/ |title=The Impossible True Story: Maria Belon & Enrique Belon |first=Jenni |last=Maier |work=crushable.com |date=21 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130301034100/http://www.crushable.com/2012/12/21/entertainment/the-impossible-true-story-maria-belon-enrique-belon/ |archive-date=1 March 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n  \nBel\u00f3n has appeared on numerous television shows, including ''[[Charlie Rose (TV show)|Charlie Rose]]'' and ''[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]'', discussing her experience of making the film and her family's experience of the tsunami. She has been outspoken regarding the fact that her story of survival is not the only one, and that she is only one of many who suffered and survived. She now works as an advocate for those still recovering from the effects of the tsunami. She has said of her experience, {{quote|The tsunami was an incredible gift. I embrace life. My whole life is extra time. There is no difference between me\u2014a Spanish woman named Mar\u00eda who is alive\u2014and thousands of moms who are under the sea. I do not deserve to be alive, but life is not fair. I feel pain and compassion for so many others who didn't come back up or lost the ones they love. My whole story is on my body. And it is wonderful because it means I am alive.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20666183,00.html |title=Maria Belon: The Impossible's Real-Life Survivor |first=Elizabeth |last=Leonard |work=[[people.com]] |date=21 January 2013 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/real-life/miracle-mum-relives-2004-tsunami-1519353 |title=Miracle mum relives 2004 Tsunami ordeal which inspired new movie 'The Impossible' |first=Tom |last=Parry |work=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]] |date=5 January 2013 |publisher=[[Trinity Mirror]] |location=[[Glasgow, Scotland|Glasgow]] |issn=0956-8069 |oclc=500344244 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-20783441 |title=BBC News - Tsunami survivor's impossible story hits the big screen |first=Rachel |last=Curtis |work=[[BBC Online]] |date=21 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://bhcourier.com/2012/12/20/george-christy-talks-impossible-juan-antonio-bayona-2004-thailand-tsunami-ewan-mcgregor-more/|title=The Impossible, Juan Antonio Bayona, The 2004 Thailand Tsunami, Ewan McGregor And More! |first=George |last=Christy |work=[[Beverly Hills Courier]] |year=2013 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref>}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|5377442}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p1NSUDYclzc Mar\u00eda Bel\u00f3n interview] (Red Carpet News Extra, posted to YouTube on 2013Jan27)\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Belon, Maria}}\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Spanish physicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish physicians]]\n[[Category:2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami]]\n[[Category:Spanish women physicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century women physicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century women physicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Mar\u00eda Bel\u00f3n\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1966|05|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Madrid]], [[Spain]]\n| nationality = {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Spanish people|Spanish]]\n| years_active = 2011\u2013present\n| occupation  = {{flatlist|\n* Spokesperson\n* advocate\n}}\n| known_for   = Surviving the 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami\n| spouse      = Enrique Alv\u00e1rez\n| children    = Lucas, Sim\u00f3n and Tom\u00e1s\n}}\n\n'''Mar\u00eda Bel\u00f3n''' (born May 12, 1966)<ref>[http://elpais.com/elpais/2013/02/13/eps/1360779765_791086.html Maria Belon story] accessed 3/21/2015</ref> is a Spanish physician and motivational speaker, known for surviving the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami]] when she was on vacation in Thailand with her husband Enrique (Quique) \u00c1lvarez<ref>[http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20666183,00.html Maria Belon: ''The Impossible''&rsquo;s Real-Life Survivor]</ref> and three sons Lucas, Sim\u00f3n and Tom\u00e1s \u00c1lvarez. She was severely injured in the tsunami and nearly died.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://voices.yahoo.com/tsunami-survivor-maria-belon-reflects-impossible-11937174.html?cat=40 |title=Tsunami Survivor Maria Belon Reflects on 'The Impossible' |first=Ben |last=Kenberr |work=voices.yahoo.com |date=14 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130124035640/http://voices.yahoo.com/tsunami-survivor-maria-belon-reflects-impossible-11937174.html?cat=40 |archive-date=24 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2252664/Boxing-Day-Tsunami-Family-relive-incredible-tale-survival-2004-tsunami-story-hits-big-screen.html |title=Boxing Day Tsunami': Family-of-five relive their incredible tale of survival in 2004 tsunami as story hits the big screen |first=Simon |last=Tomlinson |work=[[Mail Online]] |date=24 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nShe was portrayed in the 2012 film ''[[The Impossible (2012 film)|The Impossible]]'' by [[Naomi Watts]] (with the name changed to Bennett), who received a Best Actress [[Academy Award]] nomination for her performance.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://frontrowfeatures.com/2013/01/nothing-is-impossible-for-maria-belon/ |title=Maria Belon survived 'The Impossible' |first=Angela |last=Dawson |work=frontrowfeatures.com |date=3 January 2013 |accessdate=2 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130112080836/http://frontrowfeatures.com/2013/01/nothing-is-impossible-for-maria-belon/ |archive-date=12 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The family's nationality was unspecified in the film.<ref name=\"VeryAware\">{{cite web|last=Howard|first=Courtney|date=13 December 2012|url=http://veryaware.com/2012/12/interview-naomi-watts-ewan-mcgregor-j-a-bayona-sergio-g-sanchez-belen-atienza-maria-belon-talk-the-impossible/|title=INTERVIEW: Naomi Watts, Ewan McGregor, J.A. Bayona, Sergio G. S\u00e1nchez, Bel\u00e9n Atienza & Maria Belon Talk THE IMPOSSIBLE|work=Very Aware Movie Blog|accessdate=3 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121219041237/http://veryaware.com/2012/12/interview-naomi-watts-ewan-mcgregor-j-a-bayona-sergio-g-sanchez-belen-atienza-maria-belon-talk-the-impossible/|archive-date=19 December 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Movieline\">{{cite web|last=Randolph|first=Grace|date=13 December 2012|url=http://movieline.com/2012/12/13/watch-ewan-mcgregor-naomi-watts-talking-about-preparing-for-the-impossible/|title=WATCH: Ewan McGregor & Naomi Watts Talking About Preparing For 'The Impossible'|publisher=[[Movieline]]|accessdate=3 January 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Yahoo Voices\">{{cite web|date=14 December 2012|last=Kenber|first=Ben|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/tsunami-survivor-maria-belon-reflects-impossible-11937174.html|title=Tsunami Survivor Maria Belon Reflects on 'The Impossible'|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|accessdate=3 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140619151328/http://voices.yahoo.com/tsunami-survivor-maria-belon-reflects-impossible-11937174.html|archive-date=19 June 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Movies.ie\">{{cite web|date=31 December 2012|last=Hayes|first=Brogen|url=http://www.movies.ie/interviews/1186542/the_impossible__behind_the_scenes|title=THE IMPOSSIBLE \u2013 Behind The Scenes|publisher=Movies.ie|accessdate=3 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130103045504/http://www.movies.ie/Interviews/1186542/THE_IMPOSSIBLE__Behind_The_Scenes|archive-date=3 January 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nBel\u00f3n now travels around the world as an advocate for survivors of the tsunami and gives motivational speeches about how she overcame the turmoil and two years of recovery following her injuries. She studied to be a physician and also previously worked as a professor of management with the [[ESADE Business School]], and as a business consultant for companies like Pepsi. She has stated that some of her family is from the [[Canary Islands]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.grupobcc.com/files/conferenciantes/bio/Maria%20Belon.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-03-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403002912/http://www.grupobcc.com/files/conferenciantes/bio/Maria%20Belon.pdf |archivedate=2015-04-03 }} Maria Belon bio accessed 3/21/2015</ref>\n\nShe was the Spotlight Guest Speaker at the Share Iuvare Business Convention in 2015. Also in 2015 she was a speaker at the [[World Business Forum]]. In 2013 she was a guest lecturer at the Instituto de Cervantes in Gibraltar.<ref>[http://www.lomasrecomendable.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1892:maria-belon-una-vida-de-pelicula-en-world-business-forum-2015&catid=47:otros&Itemid=93 World Business Forum 2015]</ref>\n\n==Tsunami==\n{{BLP unsourced section|date=October 2016}}\nBel\u00f3n, a doctor, and her husband, Enrique \u00c1lvarez and her three sons, Lucas, Tomas and Simon were on Christmas vacation at a resort in [[Khao Lak]], Thailand. On December 26, 2004, Bel\u00f3n was at the poolside while her husband and three sons, Lucas, 10, Tom\u00e1s, 8, and Sim\u00f3n, 5, were splashing in the pool, before the family was swept apart by the tsunami.\n\nAfter the wave hit and swept her away from her family, she was able to grab hold of a tree with the aim of waiting for the tsunami to subside. While hanging on, however, she noticed her son Lucas in the distance being dragged by the current, screaming for help. She swam after him, but a second large wave occurred and she was dragged through a lot of rubble and hard sharp objects, and was critically wounded. After the tsunami calmed down, Bel\u00f3n was able to swim to land with Lucas, only to notice her many injuries. Her right leg was the most damaged, having been  completely ripped open, but she was able to dress her leg wound with palm tree leaves.\n\nBel\u00f3n and Lucas continued walking and looking for safety, but she was losing too much blood and her son had to help her walk. Lucas found a tree that the two could climb so that they would be safe from further waves. Maria was in too much pain to climb up the tree alone so Lucas, who had already climbed up, jumped down and helped her climb up the tree. After waiting on the tree for some time, the two were saved by locals from a nearby village who were coming to check the wreckage. Bel\u00f3n was then taken to a hospital, accompanied by her son.\n\nDuring his mother's recovery, Lucas was able to reunite with his father and two brothers, who happened to be in the hospital as well. Once she was stable enough to be moved, Bel\u00f3n and her family were transferred to a hospital in [[Singapore]], where she received more treatment and was finally able to return home.\n\n==Aftermath==\nBel\u00f3n is credited in the cast of the 2012 film ''[[The Impossible (2012 film)|The Impossible]]'' for providing her story and working on the set in [[Thailand]] in the same locations as the original tsunami.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2013/jan/03/reel-history-the-impossible |title=The Impossible submerges the true impact of the tsunami |first=Alex |last=von Tunzelmann |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=3 January 2013 |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group|GMG]] |location=[[London, England|London]] |issn=0261-3077 |oclc=60623878 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref> She spent time with Naomi Watts and helped her prepare for the role.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2214869/Naomi-Watts-shares-spotlight-tsunami-survivor-Maria-Madrid-premiere-The-Impossible.html |title=Naomi Watts shares the spotlight with tsunami survivor Maria at Madrid premiere of The Impossible |first=Emily |last=Sheridan |work=Mail Online |date=9 October 2012  |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref> Bel\u00f3n chose Naomi Watts to play her in the film, stating that Watts was her favorite actress after seeing the film ''[[21 Grams]]''. She worked with screenwriter [[Sergio G. S\u00e1nchez]] to ensure her story was accurately told.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.hitfix.com/the-fien-print/naomi-watts-found-real-life-inspiration-for-the-impossible |title=Naomi Watts discusses the real life inspiration for The Impossible |first=Daniel |last=Fienberg |work=[[HitFix]] |date=19 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crushable.com/2012/12/21/entertainment/the-impossible-true-story-maria-belon-enrique-belon/ |title=The Impossible True Story: Maria Belon & Enrique Belon |first=Jenni |last=Maier |work=crushable.com |date=21 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130301034100/http://www.crushable.com/2012/12/21/entertainment/the-impossible-true-story-maria-belon-enrique-belon/ |archive-date=1 March 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n  \nBel\u00f3n has appeared on numerous television shows, including ''[[Charlie Rose (TV show)|Charlie Rose]]'' and ''[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]'', discussing her experience of making the film and her family's experience of the tsunami. She has been outspoken regarding the fact that her story of survival is not the only one, and that she is only one of many who suffered and survived. She now works as an advocate for those still recovering from the effects of the tsunami. She has said of her experience, {{quote|The tsunami was an incredible gift. I embrace life. My whole life is extra time. There is no difference between me\u2014a Spanish woman named Mar\u00eda who is alive\u2014and thousands of moms who are under the sea. I do not deserve to be alive, but life is not fair. I feel pain and compassion for so many others who didn't come back up or lost the ones they love. My whole story is on my body. And it is wonderful because it means I am alive.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20666183,00.html |title=Maria Belon: The Impossible's Real-Life Survivor |first=Elizabeth |last=Leonard |work=[[people.com]] |date=21 January 2013 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/real-life/miracle-mum-relives-2004-tsunami-1519353 |title=Miracle mum relives 2004 Tsunami ordeal which inspired new movie 'The Impossible' |first=Tom |last=Parry |work=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]] |date=5 January 2013 |publisher=[[Trinity Mirror]] |location=[[Glasgow, Scotland|Glasgow]] |issn=0956-8069 |oclc=500344244 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-20783441 |title=BBC News - Tsunami survivor's impossible story hits the big screen |first=Rachel |last=Curtis |work=[[BBC Online]] |date=21 December 2012 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://bhcourier.com/2012/12/20/george-christy-talks-impossible-juan-antonio-bayona-2004-thailand-tsunami-ewan-mcgregor-more/|title=The Impossible, Juan Antonio Bayona, The 2004 Thailand Tsunami, Ewan McGregor And More! |first=George |last=Christy |work=[[Beverly Hills Courier]] |year=2013 |accessdate=2 April 2013}}</ref>}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|5377442}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p1NSUDYclzc Mar\u00eda Bel\u00f3n interview] (Red Carpet News Extra, posted to YouTube on 2013Jan27)\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Belon, Maria}}\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Spanish physicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish physicians]]\n[[Category:2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami]]\n[[Category:Spanish women physicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century women physicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century women physicians]]\n", "name_user": "94.129.246.112", "label": "vandal", "comment": "(hhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mar%C3%ADa_Bel%C3%B3n"}
